CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FConvicted killer Stephen McCullagh has
OL,8,Fclaimed he had no memory of the night
OL,9,Fhis pregnant partner was murdered but
OL,10,Fdescribed himself as "a monster."
OL,12,FNatalie McNally, 32, had been 15 weeks
OL,13,Fpregnant with their son when she was
OL,14,Fmurdered at her home in Lurgan in
OL,15,FDecember 2022.
OL,17,FStephen McCullagh, 36, of Woodland
OL,18,FGardens, Lisburn, denied the charge of
OL,19,Fmurder, but was found guilty by a jury
OL,20,Fat Belfast Crown Court earlier this
OL,21,Fyear following a five-week trial.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FA sentencing hearing on Thursday was
OL,8,Ftold McCullagh made "self-
OL,9,Fcontradictory" and "incredible"
OL,10,Fstatements to his probation officer,
OL,11,Ffirst insisting he "was convinced that
OL,12,Fhe was not guilty of the murder".
OL,14,FMcCullagh, wearing a blue T-shirt,
OL,15,Fglasses and grey trousers, was present
OL,16,Ffor the hearing, sitting in the dock,
OL,17,Fwhile Ms McNally's family watched on
OL,18,Ffrom the public gallery.
OL,26,@pD@UOUqD@NO]qD@TOUqD@_O]sD@TOUtD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FReferring to the 'offending analysis'
OL,8,Fsection of the report, Prosecuting
OL,9,Fbarrister Charles MacCreanor KC told
OL,10,FMr Justice Kinney that McCullagh
OL,11,Finitially claimed he had no memory of
OL,12,Fthe night his pregnant partner was
OL,13,Fmurdered in her own home.
OL,15,FMcCullagh said he recalled starting a
OL,16,FYouTube broadcast at 6pm, he said he
OL,17,Fwas drinking and remembered looking at
OL,18,Fphotographs of his deceased parents
OL,19,Fand his stillborn son with a previous
OL,20,Fpartner.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FHe also claimed having a bath but had
OL,8,Fno memory until he woke the following
OL,9,Fmorning - but acknowledged he 'might
OL,10,Fhave' left his house.
OL,12,FMcCullagh then told Probation he was
OL,13,Fconvinced he was not guilty of murder
OL,14,Fand was sure that McNally's ex-
OL,15,Fboyfriend was responsible.
OL,17,FHe also said that when the jury
OL,18,Freturned the guilty verdict so
OL,19,Fquickly, he only then began to suspect
OL,20,Fhe must be responsible but was unable
OL,21,Fto make any sense of the offence.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FHe said: "I don't remember feeling the
OL,8,Fneed for her to die, I'm not the type
OL,9,Fof person who seeks revenge."
OL,11,FThe court heard he described the
OL,12,Fmurder as "horrible, evil and vicious"
OL,13,Fand referred to himself as a "monster."
OL,15,FMcCullagh also told Probation "I'm
OL,16,Fsorry for what I did to that poor
OL,17,Ffamily, what I did to Natalie and what
OL,18,FI did to Dean. I would take it back in
OL,19,Fa heartbeat if I could."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FSaying there were "no mitigating
OL,8,Ffactors in this case", Mr MacCreanor
OL,9,Finstead highlighted several
OL,10,Faggravating factors including Ms
OL,11,FMcNally's vulnerability of being
OL,12,Fpregnant and living alone.
OL,14,FMr MacCreanor spoke of the "serious
OL,15,Fand extensive" injuries inflicted upon
OL,16,Fher, which amounted to 48 separate
OL,17,Fpoints of injury, as well being left
OL,18,Fface-down in a dog bowl.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FBranding this as a "sign of
OL,8,Fcallousness and wickedness", Mr
OL,9,FMacCreanor said this was "a gratuitous
OL,10,Ffeature of punishment and humiliation."
OL,12,FThe prosecutor said another "serious"
OL,13,Faggravating factor was that "not only
OL,14,Fdid he her murder his partner, but
OL,15,Falso her unborn child."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FThe prosecutor also spoke of
OL,8,FMcCullagh's planning both before and
OL,9,Fafter he killed Ms McNally including
OL,10,Fan "elaborate pretence" where he
OL,11,F"cynically presented himself as a
OL,12,Fgrieving partner" and "took advantage
OL,13,Fof her family's "kindness."
OL,15,FMr MacCreanor said that whilst he
OL,16,Faccepted McCullagh had no criminal
OL,17,Frecord, he highlighted a violent
OL,18,Fincident with a previous partner.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FThis, the Crown said, indicated
OL,8,FMcCullagh was "someone who had acted
OL,9,Fviolently in a domestic setting."
OL,11,FThe senior prosecutor also spoke of
OL,12,Fthe rates of femicide in Northern
OL,13,FIreland.
OL,15,FPointing out 30 women have been
OL,16,Fviolently killed here since 2020, Mr
OL,17,FMacCreanor said: "As part of this
OL,18,Fblight that is ongoing in Northern
OL,19,FIreland, tragically two females have
OL,20,Fbeen killed during the span of this
OL,21,Ftrial."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FRegarding the McNally family, Mr
OL,8,FMacCreanor said they had written
OL,9,FVictim Impact Statement and told Mr
OL,10,FJustice Kinney: "The level and extent
OL,11,Fof the hurt and loss they have
OL,12,Fsuffered is clearly apparent."
OL,14,FHe said that due to the multiple
OL,15,Faggravating factors and McCullagh's
OL,16,Fhigh culpability, the Tariff imposed
OL,17,Fshould be between 27 and 35 years.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FDefence barrister John Kearney KC then
OL,8,Faddressed the Judge and suggested the
OL,9,Fstarting point for sentence was a
OL,10,Flower tariff of around 15 years.
OL,12,FMr Kearney accepted the contents of
OL,13,Fhis client's pre-sentence report were
OL,14,F"self-contradictory"
OL,16,FThe defence barrister also said there
OL,17,Fwas "an absence of evidence" regarding
OL,18,Fboth the alleged degradation and
OL,19,Fhumiliation linked to the dog bowl and
OL,20,Fthe accessing of Ms McNally's phone
OL,21,Fprior to her being killed.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779455476
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murderer admits to
OL,4,Cbeing 'a monster' but no memory of
OL,5,Ckilling
OL,7,FMr Justice Kinney said he wanted time
OL,8,Fto reflect on matters and said he
OL,9,Fwould impose the Tariff upon McCullagh
OL,10,Fon June 3.
OL,12,FFollowing this, McCullagh was led from
OL,13,Fthe dock by prison staff and back into
OL,14,Fcustody.
